{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"deafceba-203c-48ca-ad4d-6e85cf5c7ac9","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is invoked via `dotnet run`. When you use `dotnet test`, it goes through the VSTest adapter layer, which doesn't support hot reload.\n\n```bash\ndotnet run -- --hotreload\n```\n\nThis will start your tests and watch for file changes. When you edit your test or source files, it will automatically re-run affected tests without a full rebuild.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0d8dde3a-f635-46ff-8a07-644d6dc8eb6f","outputTokens":124},"id":"19346c2b-d653-4ac4-8f3a-9f3362e51f23","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:45:25.675Z","parentId":"2476ca00-a2e9-4c12-9dac-f4f111939b10"}
